Descripcion_Completa:
Aventus Group growing within Spain Market and looking for a proactive HR Generalist

Location: Valencia, Spain (on-site)

Industry: Fintech Startup

About the role

We are looking for an HR Generalist to join a fast-growing fintech startup in Spain and build all HR processes from scratch. This is a hands-on role with high ownership, working closely with the CEO to prioritize and implement HR initiatives that support rapid business growth in a regulated fintech environment.

You will play a key role in shaping the company’s people strategy, culture, and operational HR foundation as the startup scales.

Key responsibilities:

- Full-cycle recruitment in Spain (tech & non-tech roles);

- Building and managing all HR processes from zero (onboarding, policies, performance, offboarding);

- Managing HR operations in a fintech startup environment;

- Office administration and coordination (documentation, employee support);

- Ensuring compliance with Spanish labor law and fintech-related requirements;

- Prioritizing HR initiatives in close collaboration with the CEO;

- Acting as the main point of contact for employees on all HR-related topics;

- Supporting scaling and team growth through structured, compliant HR solutions.

Requirements:

- 2+ years of HR experience in the Spanish market;

- Proven experience in recruitment in Spain;

- Experience working in startups and/or fintech companies (strong advantage);

- Ability to build HR processes independently from scratch;

- Strong organizational and prioritization skills;

- Fluent Spanish and English (spoken and written);

- Proactive, hands-on mindset with ownership mentality.

What we offer:

- Opportunity to build and own HR processes in a fintech startup from the ground up;

- Direct collaboration with the CEO and leadership team;

- High-impact role in a fast-growing, regulated industry;

- Dynamic, entrepreneurial environment with real growth opportunities;

- Strong global support and knowledge sharing from international colleagues across the Aventus Group.

Interested? Send your CV or LinkedIn profile to mikhail.khilo@aventusgroup.com or via Telegram: @mikhailaventus

Job Type: Full-time

Work Location: In person

You will play a key role in supporting a fast-growing Mission Critical Facilities Data Centres team at the heart of international projects. Working within Haskoning, you combine high level office and project support with exposure to complex, large scale data centre developments. This role offers real influence, international collaboration and long-term growth within a leading MCF organisation.

What you will do as Office Manager (MCF/ Data Centres)

As Office Manager (MCF/ Data Centres), you provide proactive administrative, organisational and project support to the Málaga based Mission Critical Facilities Data Centres team. You ensure smooth day to day operations, keep communication and planning on track and support high quality delivery across projects and proposals in an international environment.

In this role, your responsibilities include:

Agenda, meeting and communication management for the MCF team in Málaga;
Office coordination and administrative processes, including office logistics and facilities;
Project and proposal support, monitoring deadlines and ensuring document completeness and quality;
Coordination of visitors, travel arrangements and internal or external events;
Information management, reporting and document control, including filing and sharing updates.
Where you will work

At Haskoning, you will join an independent, employee-owned international consultancy that combines engineering, design, and consultancy services with software and technology. Our mission, "Enhancing Society Together," drives us to create a positive impact on the world.

We offer purpose-driven and challenging work in diverse international projects, leveraging our 140+ years of expertise. With over 6,800 employees in more than 25 countries, we work together to turn challenges into opportunities and make a real impact on society. We collaborate with leading clients in markets such as infrastructure, climate resilience, renewable energy, decarbonisation of industry, and sustainable mobility.

As our new Office Manager, you will become part of the team Mission Critical Facilities in Spain. Our global Mission Critical Facilities (MCF) team provides a multidisciplinary package of consultancy services for our data centre clients. We provide strategic, tactical, and operational advice to our clients, including colocation datacentres, internet service providers, and telecom companies. Our team consists of colleagues with all kinds of different expertise. For example, electrical engineering, mechanical engineering, construction, civil, structure, building, architecture, fire safety, control engineering, and security technology. Together we use our knowledge and expertise to develop integrated designs for Data Centres.

Curious about our work? Here you will find examples of some our projects.

You will join a leading market and work with a dedicated and passionate team ranked as one of the best Data Centre design & engineering teams globally.

What you bring

You are proactive, well organised and comfortable working in a dynamic, international environment. You communicate easily with different stakeholders, take ownership of your work and can balance multiple priorities while maintaining accuracy and discretion.

The key requirements for this role include:

A relevant secretarial or administrative education, providing a solid foundation for professional office and project support;
Several years of experience in an office management or project support role, enabling you to operate independently and anticipate team needs;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English and Spanish, essential for daily collaboration in an international MCF environment;
Strong digital skills, particularly in MS Word, Excel and PowerPoint, required for document management, reporting and presentations;
Experience working in a project based or consultancy environment, supporting multiple stakeholders and deadlines simultaneously. (HR/ Recruitment experience will be considered as an advantage).
What you can expect from us

At Haskoning, we believe that the well-being of our employees is essential to our shared success. That’s why we offer a comprehensive benefits package designed to support both your professional development and personal well-being.

What we offer:

A solid foundation:A permanent contract with a competitive base salary (€ 29,596 - € 42,266 p/a) and personal allowance; Bonusses based on company profit might be applicable;
Work-life balance: 23 vacation days (based on full-time employment);
Development opportunities:A wide range of training and development programs, including tailored learning paths, learning weeks, and various knowledge-sharing groups;
Informal and inclusive culture: A welcoming and open environment where people come first, diversity is embraced, team spirit is high, and everyone is approachable. And with voluntary social and sports activities, and employee networks such as Pride and Young Haskoning;
A dynamic workplacein the vibrant city centre of Málaga, including a laptop and company cell phone, and travel allowance might be applicable.
Are you our new colleague?

We would like to meet you! Click on the apply button and upload your resume and motivation letter. After receiving your application, we will contact you as soon as possible.

For more information, you can always contact Christian de Visser, Recruiter Mission Critical Facilities, at christian.de.visser@haskoning.com.

At Haskoning, we are committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered. Our mission of "Enhancing Society Together" drives us to create an environment that embraces each individual’s unique background, identity, and perspective. Regardless of your experience, background, age, gender, or other personal characteristics—you are welcome here. We believe that diversity makes us stronger and that an inclusive culture gives everyone the opportunity to grow and contribute. Read more about our ED&I initiatives on our dedicated webpage.

Due to the privacy law, please submit your application via the apply button and not via email.

